    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n## Problem\n\nWhen I set `version = vim.version.range('*')` in plugin spec, it then writes lock file with `\"version\": \">=0.0.0\"` fields.\n\nThe comparison logic in the line shown below does not handle this case and thus, sets `needs_lock_write` true.\nAs a result, it always tries to write lock file even when it does not have to.\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/65ef6cec1cb766334c59d3255595dfe523b11020/runtime/lua/vim/pack.lua#L1013\n\n(This is current head; 0.12.1 should still have this issue.)\n\nIf the version field of  lock file is string representation of VersionRange it will be parsed as VersionRange.\nSo they both can be VersionRange.  But the VersionRange meta table doesn't have `__eq`\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/65ef6cec1cb766334c59d3255595dfe523b11020/runtime/lua/vim/version.lua#L274-L282\n\nWithout __eq meta method, `VersionRange{} == VersionRange{}` returns always false.\n\n## Why it is a problem\n\nI use nix home-manager to manage my local env.\nConfig files, including `nvim-pack-lock.json`, are read-only.\nCurrently failing to write the lock file is hard error, which means I can't load rest of my config and plugins.\n\n## Workaround\n\nStop using `version = vim.version.range('*')`. leave it nil.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\ncd $(mktemp -d)\nmkdir config data\nexport XDG_CONFIG_HOME=$(pwd)/config\nexport XDG_DATA_HOME=$(pwd)/data\nnvim --clean\n:lua vim.pack.add({{src=\"https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig\",version=vim.version.range '*'}})\n:qa\nchmod 444 ./config/nvim/nvim-pack-lock.json\nnvim --clean\n:lua vim.pack.add({{src=\"https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig\",version=vim.version.range '*'}})\n```\n\nIt prints \n\n```\nE5108: Lua: ...vim-unwrapped-0.12.0/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/pack.lua:819: EACCES: permission denied: /\ntmp/tmp.LVwD2lOQoF/config/nvim/nvim-pack-lock.json\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function 'assert'\n        ...vim-unwrapped-0.12.0/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/pack.lua:819: in function 'lock_write'\n        ...vim-unwrapped-0.12.0/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/pack.lua:1027: in function 'add'\n        [string \":lua\"]:1: in main chunk\nPress ENTER or type command to continue\n```\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo error/ It does not try to write when it would cause no diff.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim does not have vim.pack API\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux 6.6.87.2-microsoft-standard-WSL2\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nnix unstable",
