            "body": "Thanks for the issue!\n\nIndeed I can reproduce this. The culprit here is indeed that `vim.version.range('*') == vim.version.range('*')` returns `false`.\n\nI think the most reasonable and wider useful solution here is to add the ability to check for equality of two `vim.version.range()`. It should be possible as \"equal if both `from` and `to` are equal\" and is relatively straightforward.",
